{"title_page": "Faldir Chahbari", "text_new": "{{Infobox martial artist\n| name            = Faldir Chahbari \n| native_name     = \u0641\u0644\u062f\u064a\u0631 \u0634\u0647\u0628\u0631\u064a\n| native_name_lang= ar\n| image           = \n| image_size      = \n| caption         = \n| birth_name      = \n| other_names     = Fast\n| nationality     = {{flagicon|MAR}} [[Moroccan people|Moroccan]] <br> {{flagicon|NED}} [[Dutch people|Dutch]]\n| birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|1979|8|30|mf=y}}\n| birth_place     = Ijarmauas, Morocco\n| fighting_out_of = [[Brummen]], [[Netherlands]]\n| death_date      = \n| death_place     = \n| height          = {{height|m=1.81|precision=0}}\n| weight          = {{convert|70|kg|lb stlb|0|abbr=on}}\n| weight_class    = [[Welterweight]]\n| style           = [[Kickboxing]], [[Muay Thai]]\n| stance          =\n| team            = KB Brummen <br> Team Beast of the East\n| trainer         = Kenneth Macnack/Wim Scharrenberg\n| years_active    = 1997\u2013present\n| kickbox_win     = 101\n| kickbox_kowin   = 24\n| kickbox_loss    = 12\n| kickbox_koloss  =\n| kickbox_draw    = 4\n| kickbox_nc      = \n| other           = \n| occupation      = \n| spouse          = \n| relatives       = \n| students        = \n| university      =\n| website         = \n| boxrec          =\n| sherdog         =\n| updated         = December 15, 2013\n}}\n\n'''\"Fast\" Faldir Chahbari''' ([[Arabic language|Arabic:]] \u0641\u0644\u062f\u064a\u0631 \u0634\u0647\u0628\u0631\u064a; born August 30, 1979) is [[Moroccan-Dutch]] [[welterweight]] [[kickboxer]], fighting out of [[Brummen]], [[Netherlands]]. He a x2 [[Muay Thai]] amateur world champion and is the former (and first ever) World Full Contact Association (W.F.C.A.) [[Muay Thai|Thai-boxing]] junior middleweight world champion.\n\n==Biography==\n\nFaldir Chahbari began boxing at the Kickboxing brummen gym in 1994, and started in youth matches 2 years later. Trained at the time by Kenneth Macnack, he now has his own gym giving training sessions in Zutphen and Apeldoorn. He has only one functioning eye, after losing the use of the other eye in an accident as a child.\n\n==Career==\n\nChahbari spent most of his early career fighting in the [[Netherlands]].  He won his first major title at the Battle of Arnhem II event in 2001 where he won the I.K.B.O. European title.<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.nikko-sportsvideo.com/downloads/fightcards/KB202.pdf \n |title=Battle of Arnhem II (Fight Card) \n |accessdate=2011-02-20 \n |publisher=www.nikko-sportsvideo.com \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714183127/http://www.nikko-sportsvideo.com/downloads/fightcards/KB202.pdf \n |archivedate=2011-07-14 \n}}</ref>  He followed up this victory by winning the W.P.K.L. Dutch national title the very next year.  In 2004 he added another national title to his resume, this time with the W.F.C.A., following up with the European version in 2005 with a win against the talented knockout specialist [[Murat Direk\u00e7i]].<ref>{{cite web\n| url=http://www.kickbox.nl/forums/showthread.php?s=&threadid=7966\n| title=Faldir Chahbari vs Murat Direcki in Nijmegen!\n| last= \n| first= \n| accessdate=2011-02-20\n| publisher=www.kickbox.nl\n}}</ref>  Between the years 2000 and 2006 he picked up some decent wins, defeating the likes of [[Marco Piqu\u00e9]] and [[Gago Drago]] and retained his W.P.K.L. and W.F.C.A. national and European titles in other bouts.  He also had a successful amateur career, winning two gold medals at the W.M.F. world championships held in [[Bangkok, Thailand]] and a silver at the [[World Association of Kickboxing Organizations|W.A.K.O]] world championships held in [[Agadir, Morocco]].\n  \nIn 2006 Chahbari entered the [[K-1 MAX Netherlands 2006 The Road to Tokyo|K-1 MAX Netherlands 2006]] in a bid to qualify for a reserve fight at the [[K-1 World MAX 2006 World Championship Final|K-1 World MAX 2006 Final]],  He made his way through to the K-1 MAX Netherlands final in [[Utrecht]] but had his dreams of a flight to [[Yokohama]] scuppered by the experienced [[Rayen Simson]] who defeated him after an extension round.<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.sherdog.net/forums/f42/spoiler-results-k-1-max-holland-355689/ \n |title=SPOILER! results K-1 MAX Holland \n |accessdate=2011-02-20 \n |publisher=www.sherdog.net \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724062558/http://www.sherdog.net/forums/f42/spoiler-results-k-1-max-holland-355689/ \n |archivedate=2011-07-24 \n}}</ref>  The following year he retained his W.F.C.A. European title by knocking out Chris Venrooij with a knee after just 15 seconds.<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.kbzutphen.nl/page.php?id=66 \n |title=Website Kickboxing Zutphen - Faldir CHAHBARI wint van Chris van (Dutch Language) \n |accessdate=2011-02-20 \n |publisher=www.kbzutphen.nl \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070819181146/http://www.kbzutphen.nl/page.php?id=66 \n |archivedate=2007-08-19 \n}}</ref>  Although he had missed out on a place at the K-1 MAX final the previous year, Chahbari did make his way to Japan where he took part in a number of [[Shoot boxing|Shoot Boxing]] events in [[Tokyo]], winning one and losing one.  In 2008, as W.F.C.A. European champion he met multiple world champion [[Albert Kraus]], defeating him over five rounds to become the first ever W.F.C.A. world title holder at junior middleweight (under 70 [[kg]]).  He held on to the belt until early 2010 when he lost to the highly decorated [[Andy Souwer]] who became the new champion.<ref>{{cite web\n| url=http://www.mmalinker.com/forum/k1-kickboxing-boxing/souwer-vs-chahbari-beast-of-the-east-spoilers-t48380-15.html\n| title=Souwer vs. Chahbari - Beast of the East *SPOILERS* : K1 Kickboxing ...\n| last= \n| first= \n| accessdate=2011-02-20\n| publisher=www.mmalinker.com\n}}</ref>  Since 2006 he has suffered more defeats as the competition has got tougher, losing to the likes of [[Buakaw Por. Pramuk]] and [[Giorgio Petrosyan]], but has still shown himself to be a contender winning a KlasH tournament late in 2010 by defeating [[Shemsi Beqiri]].<ref>{{cite web\n| url=http://www.groundandpound.de/allgemein/veranstaltungsberichte/news/ergebnisse-mix-fight-gala-xi/\n| title=Mix Fight Gala XI: K-1 Ergebnisse . Veranstaltungsberichte ... (German Language)\n| last= \n| first= \n| accessdate=2011-02-20\n| publisher=www.groundandpound.de\n}}</ref>\n\n==Titles==\n\n'''Professional'''<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.fightingball.tv/faldir_chahbari_english?fightingball_tv=e44359aaedf3cab909a960a47ed2a843 \n |title=Profile page Faldir Chahbari \n |accessdate=2011-02-20 \n |publisher=www.fightingball.tv \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111007165724/http://www.fightingball.tv/faldir_chahbari_english?fightingball_tv=e44359aaedf3cab909a960a47ed2a843 \n |archivedate=2011-10-07 \n}}</ref> \n*2010 Mix Fight Gala 11 - KlasH tournament champion -72.5&nbsp;kg\n*2008-10 W.F.C.A. Thai-boxing world champion -69.85&nbsp;kg (1 title defence)\n*2006 [[K-1 MAX Netherlands 2006 The Road to Tokyo|K-1 MAX Netherlands 2006]] runner up -70&nbsp;kg\n*2004-07 W.F.C.A. Thai-boxing European champion -69.85&nbsp;kg\n*2004-07 W.F.C.A. Thai-boxing Dutch champion -69.85&nbsp;kg\n*2002-03 W.P.K.L. Thai-boxing Dutch champion -67&nbsp;kg\n*2001 I.K.B.O. Thai-boxing European champion -67&nbsp;kg\n\n'''Amateur'''<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.fightingball.tv/faldir_chahbari_english?fightingball_tv=e44359aaedf3cab909a960a47ed2a843 \n |title=Profile page Faldir Chahbari \n |accessdate=2011-02-20 \n |publisher=www.fightingball.tv \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111007165724/http://www.fightingball.tv/faldir_chahbari_english?fightingball_tv=e44359aaedf3cab909a960a47ed2a843 \n |archivedate=2011-10-07 \n}}</ref> \n*2005 [[W.A.K.O. World Championships 2005 (Agadir)|W.A.K.O. World Championships in Agadir, Morocco]] [[Image:Med 2.png|Silver]] -71&nbsp;kg (Thai-Boxing) \n*2005 W.M.F. World Championships [[Image:Med 1.png|Gold]] -70&nbsp;kg (Muay Thai)\n*2003 W.M.F. World Championships [[Image:Med 1.png|Gold]] -67&nbsp;kg (Muay Thai)\n\n== Kickboxing record ==\n{| class=\"toccolours\" width=95% style=\"clear:both; margin:1.5em auto; font-size:85%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=2 style=\"background:#A9A9A9\" | <span style=\"color:white;\">Kickboxing Record<ref>{{cite web\n| url=http://www.k-1fans.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=39670\n| title=Faldir Chahbari (Profile & Record)\n| last= \n| first= \n| accessdate=2011-02-20\n| publisher=www.k-1fans.com\n}}</ref></span>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|<div class=\"NavFrame\">\n<div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"background:white; \"><span style=\"color:black;\">'''80 Wins''' (23 (T)KO's), '''12 Losses''', '''3 Draws''', '''1 No Contest'''</span></div>\n<div class=\"NavContent\" style=\"text-align:left; display:collapse;\">\n{|class=\"wikitable\" width=\"100%\"\n|- align=\"center\"  bgcolor=\"#dddddd\"\n| '''Date''' || '''Result''' || '''Opponent''' || '''Event''' || '''Location''' || '''Method''' || '''Round''' || '''Time'''\n|- align=\"center\"  bgcolor=\"#CCFFCC\"\n| 2013-04-13 ||Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|CRO}} [[Goran Borovi\u0107]] || Beast of the East || [[Zutphen, Netherlands]] || Decision ||5  ||3:00 \n|-\n! style=background:white colspan=9 |{{small| Wins '''King of the Ring''' Muay Thai rules world title -72.5&nbsp;kg.}}\n|-\n|- align=\"center\"  bgcolor=\"#CCFFCC\"\n| 2013-02-17 ||Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|ESP}} Antonio Gomez || <ref>[http://www.wfca.info/uitslagen17022013denhaag.html 2013-02-17 Arnhem]</ref> || [[Arnhem, Netherlands]] || Decision ||3  ||3:00 \n|-\n|- align=\"center\"  bgcolor=\"#CCFFCC\"\n| 2012-05-27 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|THA}} [[Bovy Sor Udomson]] || SLAMM: Nederland vs. Thailand VII || Almere, Netherlands || Decision (Unanimous) || 5 || 3:00\n|- align=\"center\"  bgcolor=\"#CCFFCC\"\n| 2011-11-19 || Win ||align=