 Fights]] || [[Amsterdam, Netherlands]] || Ext.R Decision (Unanimous) || 4 || 3:00\n|-\n|- align=\"center\"  bgcolor=\"#CCFFCC\"\n| 2009-07-25 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|POR}} Ricardo Fernandes || Night of the Stars || [[Tetouan|Tetouan, Morocco]] || Decision || 3 || 3:00\n|-\n|- align=\"center\"  bgcolor=\"#CCFFCC\"\n| 2009-06-13 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|MAR}} [[Hafid el Boustati]] || Gentlemen Fight Night 6 || [[Tilburg, Netherlands]] || Decision (Unanimous) || 3 || 3:00\n|-\n|- align=\"center\"  bgcolor=\"#FFBBBB\"\n| 2009-05-16 || Loss ||align=left|{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Giorgio Petrosyan]] || [[It's Showtime 2009 Amsterdam]] || [[Amsterdam, Netherlands]] || Decision (Unanimous) || 3 || 3:00\n|-\n|- align=\"center\"  bgcolor=\"#CCFFCC\"\n| 2009-01-24 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|GER}} Mohammed Gur || Beast of the East 2009 || [[Zutphen, Netherlands]] || Decision || 3 || 3:00\n|-\n! style=background:white colspan=9 |{{small|Retains W.F.C.A. Thai-boxing junior middleweight world title -69.85&nbsp;kg.}}\n|-\n|- align=\"center\"  bgcolor=\"#CCFFCC\"\n| 2008-11-29 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|THA}} [[Orono Wor Petchpun]] || [[It's Showtime 2008 Eindhoven]] || [[Eindhoven, Netherlands]] || Decision (Majority) || 3 || 3:00\n|-\n|- align=\"center\"  bgcolor=\"#CCFFCC\"\n| 2008-07-06 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|GEO}} [[Davit Kiria]] || Ultimate Glory 8 || [[Nijmegen, Netherlands]] || TKO (Doc Stop/Cut) || 2 || \n|-\n|- align=\"center\"  bgcolor=\"#FFBBBB\"\n| 2008-04-26 || Loss ||align=left|{{flagicon|THA}} [[Buakaw Por. Pramuk]] || [[K-1 World Grand Prix 2008 in Amsterdam|K-1 World GP 2008 Amsterdam]], Super Fight || [[Amsterdam, Netherlands]] || Decision (Split) || 3 || 3:00\n|-\n|- align=\"center\"  bgcolor=\"#c5d2ea\"\n| 2008-03-15 || Draw ||align=left|{{flagicon|TUR}} [[Murat Direk\u00e7i]] || [[Balans: It\u2019s Showtime 75MAX Trophy Final 2008|It's Showtime 75MAX Trophy Final 2008]], Super Fight || [['s-Hertogenbosch|'s-Hertogenbosch, Netherlands]] ||