{"title_page": "2019 Dayton shooting", "text_new": "{{short description|Mass shooting in Dayton, Ohio, United States of America}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use American English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox civilian attack\n| title         = 2019 Dayton shooting\n| partof        = \n| image         = Ned_Peppers_Bar_after_2019_Dayton_shooting.jpg\n| image_size    = \n| image_upright = 1.25\n| alt           = \n| caption       = Ned Peppers Bar the day after the shooting\n| map           = Map of 2019 Dayton Shooting.svg\n| map_size      = \n| map_alt       = \n| map_caption   = Map of the events of the shooting within the [[Oregon Historic District]]\n| location      = 419 East 5th Street<br />[[Dayton, Ohio]], United States\n| target        = \n| coordinates   = {{coord|39.7572|-84.1843|type:event_region:US-OH|display=it}}\n| date          = {{Start date|2019|8|4}}\n| time          = 1:05 a.m.\n| timezone      = [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]] [[UTC\u221204:00]]\n| type          = [[Mass shooting]]\n| weapons       = AR-15 style pistol using [[.223 Remington]] with a 100-round [[drum magazine]]<ref name=\"WSJ20190805\" /><ref name=Loophole/>\n| fatalities    = 10 (including the perpetrator)\n| injuries      = 27 (17 from gunfire)<ref name=\"AP17\" /><ref name=DPD.190815/>\n| victims       = <!-- or | victim = -->\n| assailants    = \n| perp          = Connor Stephen Betts\n| numparts      = <!-- or | numpart = -->\n| dfens         = <!-- or | dfen = -->\n| website       = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| module        = \n}}\n\nOn August 4, 2019, Connor Stephen Betts, 24, fatally shot nine people and wounded 17 others near the entrance of the Ned Peppers Bar in [[Dayton, Ohio]].<ref name=\"AP17\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcbayarea.com/news/national-international/Dayton-Gunman-Deadly-Mass-Shooting-539291401.html|title=Ohio Shooter Hit 26 People in Half a Minute|date=13 August 2019|publisher=[[Associated Press]]}}</ref> Betts was fatally shot by responding police officers 32 seconds after his first shot.<ref name=\"Sec\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.wlwt.com/article/police-gunman-s-sister-among-9-killed-in-dayton-mass-shooting/28599430|quote=According to Dayton Police Chief Richard Biehl, officers engaged the suspect within 20 seconds of hearing shots fired. Thirty seconds after the gunman began shooting, he was shot and killed by first responders, Biehl said.|title=Police: Gunman's sister among 9 killed in Dayton mass shooting|publisher=WLWT 5|date=August 4, 2019|accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref> An additional ten persons were injured by other causes, bringing the total number of wounded to 27.<ref name=\"AP17\" />\n\nA search of the shooter's home found evidence that showed an interest in violence and [[mass shootings]] and he had expressed a desire to commit one. Despite describing himself as a [[leftist]] and voicing his support for [[Antifa (United States)|Antifa]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/us/live-news/el-paso-dayton-shootings-august-2019/h_c3fe4a1d2b04da849422f817647227ab |title=The Dayton shooter had an extreme left Twitter feed |first1=Paul |last1=Murphy |first2=Konstantin |last2=Toropin |date=2019-08-05 |website=[[CNN]] |access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref> a preliminary assessment did not indicate that Betts had a racial or political motive.<ref name=\"Pre\"/> The attack occurred just 13 hours after an [[2019 El Paso shooting|earlier mass shooting in El Paso, Texas]].<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/aug/04/mass-shootings-el-paso-texas-dayton-ohio|title=Thirty dead in 13 hours: US reckons with back-to-back mass shootings|first1=Sam Levin Oliver|last1=Laughland|first2=Joanna Walters in New|last2=York|date=August 5, 2019|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref>\n\n==Attack==\nTwo hours before the attack, the gunman was seen entering a bar with his sibling<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/amberjamieson/dayton-shooting-victims|title=The Victims Of The Dayton Mass Shooting Include The Gunman\u2019s Brother And 8 Others|publisher=[[BuzzFeed News]]|date=August 4, 2019|access-date=August 12, 2019}}</ref> and a friend in the downtown [[Oregon Historic District]] of Dayton. At about 12:13&nbsp;a.m., he split from the two and was recorded leaving the bar.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/08/06/us/surveillance-video-connor-betts-in-bar/index.html |title=Exclusive video shows Dayton gunman Connor Betts in bar in the hours before shooting |first1=Noah |last1=Gray |first2=Curt |last2=Devine |first3=Patricia |last3=DiCarlo |first4=Mark |last4=Morales |website=[[CNN]] |date=August 6, 2019 |accessdate=August 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAt 1:05&nbsp;a.m., eyewitnesses reported that a man opened fire at the entrance of Ned Peppers Bar in the Oregon Historic District.<ref name=\"Heavy\">{{Cite web|url=https://heavy.com/news/2019/08/dayton-ohio-active-shooter-shooting/|title=Dayton Mass Shooting: Multiple Dead at Ned Peppers Bar in Ohio|publisher=Heavy.com|date=August 4, 2019|accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref> He was carrying a firearm that included part of a [[Semi-automatic pistol|semi-automatic]] AM-15 (based on the [[AR-15 style rifle|AR-15)]]<ref name=\"WSJ20190805\">{{cite news |last1=Kesling |first1=Ben |title=Dayton Shooter Used AR-15 Pistol, Smaller Version of Popular Rifle |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/dayton-shooter-used-ar-15-pistol-smaller-version-of-popular-rifle-11565045046 |accessdate=August 5, 2019 |work=The Wall Street Journal |url-access=limited |date=August 5, 2019}}</ref><ref name=PohlmanWKRC>{{cite news |url=https://local12.com/news/duane-is-that-right/key-section-of-weapon-used-in-dayton-mass-shooting-manufactured-in-tri-state |title=Key section of weapon used in Dayton mass shooting manufactured in Tri-State |first=Duane |last=Pohlman |website=local12.com |publisher=[[WKRC-TV]] |date=August 5, 2019 |accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref> in a [[pistol]] configuration with a shortened [[Barrel (firearm)|barrel]], chambered in [[.223 Remington|.223 caliber]] ammunition and equipped with a 100-round [[drum magazine]].<ref name=Loophole/><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2019/08/05/us/gun-laws-el-paso-dayton-shootings.html |title=How State Laws Allowed Military-Style Guns Used in Dayton and El Paso Shootings |first1=Larry |last1=Buchanan |first2=K.K. Rebecca |last2=Lai |website=[[The New York Times]] |url-access=limited |date=August 5, 2019 |accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref> He fired 41 rounds into the crowd in less than 30 seconds, fatally shooting nine people.<ref name=\"obession\" /><ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|url=https://www.wmra.org/post/9-killed-least-16-injured-shooting-dayton-ohio#stream/0|title=9 Killed, 26 Injured In Shooting In Dayton, Ohio|date=August 4, 2019|publisher=[[WMRA]]|access-date=August 4, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"CNN-WhatWeKnow\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/us/live-news/ohio-shooting/index.html|title=What we know about the Dayton shooting|website=|publisher=CNN|last=Kottasova|first=Ivana|date=August 4, 2019|access-date=August 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAccording to Dayton Police Chief Richard Biehl, 20 seconds after the shooting began,<ref name=\"Sec\"/> law enforcement officers already on the scene engaged the gunman.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/us/live-news/ohio-shooting/index.html|title=Mass shooting in Dayton, Ohio|publisher=[[CNN]]|date=August 4, 2019|access-date=August 4, 2019}}</ref> Within 32 seconds after the first shots were fired,<ref name=\"AP17\"/> the gunman was shot dead.<ref name=\"BBC\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-49224816|title=Dayton shooting: Nine confirmed killed, gunman also dead|date=2019-08-04|access-date=2019-08-04|publisher=[[BBC]]}}</ref> An autopsy report released on December 6, 2019, showed that Betts was hit with 30 rounds.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cincinnati.com/story/news/2019/12/06/dayton-shooters-autopsy-lists-30-gunshot-wounds/4357662002/|title=Autopsy reveals Dayton shooter was hit with 30 rounds in 32 seconds|first=Madeline|last=Mitchell|website=Cincinnati.com}}</ref> Local police evacuated many nearby night venues, and warned Dayton residents to stay away from the Oregon Historic District.<ref name=\"BBC\" />\n\n==Victims==\n[[File:Vigil for Shooting Victims, Dayton (OH)05-(1b) (48464805991).jpg|thumb|Vigil for the victims, August 5, 2019]]\n[[Miami Valley Hospital]] received 16 victims from the shooting, of which five were admitted, one in critical condition. [[Kettering Health Network]], comprising nine hospitals in the area, received nine victims, with three in serious condition and three in fair condition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/active-shooter-incident-investigated-dayton-ohio-police/story?id=64763090|title=At least 9 dead, 26 injured in mass shooting in downtown Dayton; suspect identified|last=Osborne|first=Mark|publisher=ABC News|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref> By 10:00&nbsp;a.m. on the same day, 15 of 27 hospitalized people had been discharged.<ref name=\"BBC\" />\nOf the injured, 17 were shot.\n\nPolice reported that all the fatalities occurred outside the bar on East 5th Street,<ref name=\"BBC\" /> and that the shooter's 22-year-old sibling was among those killed.<ref>\n*{{Cite news |url=https://heavy.com/news/2019/08/connor-betts-sister-megan-betts/ |title=Megan Betts, Connor Betts' Sister, Found Dead |first=Paul |last=Farrell |date=August 4, 2019 |accessdate=August 4, 2019 |publisher=[[Heavy.com]]}}\n*{{cite news |last1=Feldman |first1=Kate |title=Nine dead, at least 26 injured in Dayton, Ohio, after 24-year-old gunman in body armor opens fire |url=https://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/ny-dayton-ohio-mass-shooting-20190804-pmcnqkoid5defoiy6hhngi2pfm-story.html |accessdate=August 4, 2019 |work=Daily News |date=August 4, 2019}}\n*{{cite news |url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/jordan-cofer-trans-victim-dayton-mass-shooting/amp |title=Remembering Jordan Cofer, Trans Victim of the Dayton Mass Shooting |work=[[Teen Vogue]] |first=Sarah Emily |last=Baum |date=August 12, 2019 |access-date=August 13, 2019}}</ref> Investigators are trying to determine if the gunman intentionally or accidentally killed his sibling, who was among the first victims.<ref>{{cite news |work=[[USA Today]] |date=August 5, 2019 |first=Anne |last=Saker |title=Dayton shooting: Gunman killed his sister, but was the 'sororicide' intentional? |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2019/08/05/dayton-shooting-too-early-tell-reasons-connor-betts-killed-sister/1928195001/}}</ref>\n\nThe nine dead include five males and four females, six black and three white. Four of the dead were in their 20s, four more were in their 30s, and one was 57.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/04/us/dayton-ohio-shooting.html |work=[[The New York Times]] |title=Dayton, Ohio, Shooting: Victims Identified; Live Updates |date=August 4, 2019 |first1=Timothy |last1=Williams |first2=Farah |last2=Stockman |access-date=August 4, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bostonherald.com/2019/08/04/the-latest-9-killed-at-least-16-hurt-in-ohio-shooting/ |work=[[Boston Herald]] |title=The Latest: Neighbors recall Ohio shooter being 'good kid' |date=August 4, 2019 |access-date=August 4, 2019}}</ref> Two of the victims who died were also shot by police.<ref name=\"AP17\"/><ref name=DPD.190815>{{cite tweet |user=DaytonPolice |number=1162080211229429762 |date=August 15, 2019 |title=Dr. Harshbarger - There were two victims who were hit additionally as a result of the law enforcement response.}}</ref><ref>\n*{{cite news|url=https://www.wcpo.com/news/national/dayton-shooting-police-still-trying-to-determine-motive-say-14-injured-suffered-gunshot-wounds|title=Dayton shooting: Police still trying to determine motive, say 14 injured suffered gunshot wounds|publisher=[[WCPO 9]]|date=August 5, 2019|access-date=August 6, 2019}}\n*{{cite tweet |user=DaytonPolice |number=1161355791275831298 |date=August 13, 2019 |title=Chief Biehl: We had 9 killed by gunshot wounds and 17 others injured by gunshots.}}</ref> An autopsy showed that a woman who was shot by Betts was already bleeding from a fatal gunshot wound when she was struck by two bullets which were fired by police. Had she not been suffering from fatal injuries, one of the bullets which were fired by police would have been lethal. The second victim was shot by Betts multiple times and sustained a superficial gunshot wound from police. As a result of those findings, Montgomery County Coroner Dr. Kent Harshbarger ruled that the deaths were caused by Betts and were not the result of police gunfire.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cincinnati.com/story/news/2019/08/15/coroner-release-more-autopsy-information-dayton-shooting/2018778001/|title=Coroner: 2 victims of Dayton mass shooting struck by rounds from shooter and police|first1=Sarah|last1=Brookbank|first2=Kevin|last2=Grasha|first3=Chris|last3=Mayhew|website=Cincinnati.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wcpo.com/news/mass-shooting/none-of-dayton-victims-killed-by-police-fire-coroner-says|title=None of nine Dayton victims killed by police fire, coroner says|date=August 15, 2019|website=WCPO}}</ref>\n\n==Perpetrator==\nSoon after the attack, police identified the gunman as '''Connor Stephen Betts''',<!--The name of the perpetrator is in BOLD to indicate that [[Connor Stephen Betts]] is a redirect to the article, and thus supports the principle of least astonishment when a redirected reader arrives. See MOS:BOLD. Do not remove, please.--><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aol.com/article/news/2019/08/14/dayton-mass-shooter-connor-betts-obituary/23793379/|title=Family of Dayton mass shooter Connor Betts remembers him as 'funny,' 'intelligent' in obituary|last=Staff|first=A. O. L.|website=AOL.com|language=en|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref> a 24-year-old who lived in [[Bellbrook, Ohio]].<ref name=\"BBC\" /><ref>\n*{{cite news |title=Connor Betts' Family: 5 Fast Facts You Need to Know |url=https://heavy.com/news/2019/08/connor-betts-family-parents-mother-father/ |accessdate=10 August 2019 |agency=Heavy |date=10 August 2019}}\n*{{cite news|url=https://abc7chicago.com/connor-stephen-betts-idd-as-dayton-suspected-shooter-sources/5442328/|title=Connor Stephen Betts identified as Dayton suspected shooter; Suspect's sister found dead, sources say|date=August 4, 2019|publisher=ABC-7|location=Chicago|accessdate=August 4, 2019}}\n*{{cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/live-news/dayton-ohio-shooting-suspect-connor-betts-9-killed-mass-shooting-today-2019-08-04-live-updates/|title=9 killed in Dayton, Ohio, in second U.S. mass shooting in 24 hours|date=August 4, 2019|accessdate=August 4, 2019|publisher=CBS News|agency=Associated Press}}</ref>  According to police, he had minor traffic offenses on his record.<ref name=\"Cincinnati\" /><ref>\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/connor-betts-24-idd-as-dayton-ohio-shooter|title=Dayton Shooter Murdered Sister in Attack, Officials Say|last1=Nadeau|first1=Barbie Latza|last2=Daly|first2=Michael|date=August 4, 2019|via=thedailybeast.com}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/08/05/us/connor-betts-dayton-shooting-profile/index.html|title=Classmates say Dayton gunman had a 'hit list' in high school|last1=Murphy|first1=Paul P.|last2=Ash|first2=Audrey|publisher=CNN|last3=Crespo|first3=Gisela}}</ref>\n\nBetts made online references about [[Satan]] and described himself as a leftist and [[Antifa (United States)|Antifa]] sympathizer.<ref name=\"Satan\">{{cite web|url=https://www.snopes.com/fact-check/dayton-shooter-warren/|title=Was Dayton Mass Shooter a Self-Described 'Pro-Satan Leftist Who Supported Elizabeth Warren'?|website=[[Snopes]]|date=August 5, 2019|accessdate=August 5, 2019|first=Alex|last=Kasprak}}</ref><ref name=\"heavy5\">{{cite web |url=https://heavy.com/news/2019/08/connor-betts-twitter-politics-social-media/ |title=Connor Betts: Twitter Posts on Being a Leftist, Guns |publisher=[[Heavy.com]] |last=McBride |first=Jessica |date=August 4, 2019 |accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"MurphyFeed\">{{cite news |last1=Murphy |first1=Paul P. |last2=Toropin |first2=Konstantin |last3=Griffin |first3=Drew |last4=Bronstein |first4=Scott |title=Dayton shooter appeared to have leftist Twitter feed |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/08/05/us/connor-betts-dayton-shooting-profile/index.html |accessdate=August 6, 2019 |publisher=CNN |date=August 5, 2019}}</ref>  In the hours before he opened fire in Dayton, he \"liked\" a post in favor of [[Gun control in the United States|gun control]], and several concerning the El Paso shooting, including a tweet that called the El Paso shooter a \"terrorist\" and a \"[[white supremacist]].\"<ref name=\"MurphyFeed\" /> On August 10, [[ABC News]] quoted officials as stating that the gunman had [[misogynist]] views which were much more extreme than his political views.<ref name=\"exmis\">{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/alleged-dayton-gunman-connor-betts-showed-signs-misogyny/story?id=64826324|title=Alleged Dayton gunman showed signs of misogyny, mirroring a grim pattern for shooters|last1=Svokos|first1=Alexandra|website=[[ABC News]]|accessdate=August 14, 2019}}</ref> Betts was also known to have been in support of presidential candidates [[Elizabeth Warren]] and [[Bernie Sanders]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2019/08/07/dayton-shooting-what-do-we-know-connor-betts-politics/1943289001/|title=Dayton shooting: What we know about the gunman's politics|last=Knight|first=Keith BieryGolick and Cameron|website=USA TODAY|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/us/live-news/el-paso-dayton-shootings-august-2019/h_c3fe4a1d2b04da849422f817647227ab|title=The Dayton shooter had an extreme left Twitter feed|author1=Meg Wagner |author2=Elise Hammond |author3=Mike Hayes |author4=Veronica Rocha|date=2019-08-05|website=CNN|language=en|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref>\n\nTwo former high school classmates said Betts was suspended from [[Bellbrook High School]] after he made lists of other students he wanted to kill and rape.<ref name=\"Kill-list\">{{cite news |last1=Biesecker |first1=Michael |last2=Carr Smyth |first2=Julie |title=Classmates: Ohio shooter kept a 'hit list' and a 'rape list' |url=https://news.yahoo.com/classmates-ohio-shooter-kept-hit-033305480.html |accessdate=August 5, 2019 |agency=Associated Press |date=August 5, 2019}}</ref> The \"hit list\" was discovered in early 2012 and resulted in a police investigation.<ref name=\"Kill-list\" /> He was previously bullied and had planned to shoot up the school, a classmate said.<ref name=Cincinnati>{{cite web |url=https://www.cincinnati.com/story/news/2019/08/04/dayton-shooting-what-we-know-gunman/1916121001/ |title=Dayton shooting: What we know about the gunman |work=[[Cincinnati Enquirer]] |date=August 4, 2019 |last1=Trombly |first1=Monroe |last2=Baldas |first2=Tresa |accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref> Over the past year, the gunman had performed live vocals for a [[pornogrind]] band called Menstrual Munchies, a genre which ''[[Vice News]]'' described as a \"misogynistic, male-dominated\" music scene, and [[Buzzfeed]] described as focused on gore, violence, and necrophilia, and known for its dark, satirical themes of sexual violence delivered for shock value.<ref>\n*{{cite news |work=[[BuzzFeed News]] |date=August 5, 2019 |first=Ellie |last=Hall |title=The Dayton Shooter Was The Lead Singer Of A \"Pornogrind\" Metal Band |url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/ellievhall/dayton-shooter-pornogrind-band}}\n*{{Cite news |title=Exclusive: Dayton Shooter Was in a \"Pornogrind\" Band That Released Songs About Raping and Killing Women |work=[[Vice News]] |date=August 5, 2019 |accessdate=August 5, 2019 |url=https://news.vice.com/en_us/article/j5yekp/exclusive-dayton-shooter-was-in-a-pornogrind-band-that-released-songs-about-raping-and-killing-women}}</ref> His high school girlfriend said he complained of visual and auditory [[hallucination]]s and [[psychosis]], and was afraid of developing [[schizophrenia]].<ref>\n*{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/police-chief-it-seems-to-defy-believability-that-dayton-shooter-would-kill-his-own-sister/2019/08/05/920a895c-b79e-11e9-b3b4-2bb69e8c4e39_story.html |title=Ex-girlfriend says Dayton shooter heard voices, talked about 'dark, evil things' |work=[[The Washington Post]] |date=August 5, 2019 |first1=Emily |last1=Davies |first2=Tim |last2=Craig |first3=Hannah |last3=Natanson |access-date=August 5, 2019}}\n*{{cite news |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=August 6, 2019 |agency=[[Associated Press]] |title='He trusted me': ex-girlfriend says Ohio gunman wrestled with dark thoughts |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2019/aug/06/he-trusted-me-ex-girlfriend-reveals-ohio-gunmans-darkest-thoughts}}</ref>\n\n== Investigation ==\nOn August 4, police and the [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] searched the shooter's home and found evidence that showed an interest in violence and mass shootings and that he had expressed a desire to commit a mass shooting.<ref name=\"obession\">{{cite news |last1=Murphy |first1=Paul |title=Dayton shooter had an obsession with violence and mass shootings, police say |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/08/05/us/connor-betts-dayton-shooting-profile/index.html |accessdate=31 August 2019 |publisher=CNN |date=August 7, 2019}}</ref> A preliminary assessment did not indicate the shooter had a racial or political motive.<ref name=\"Pre\" /> {{As of|2019|08|5|df=US}}, police investigators stated that the investigation is ongoing and that they are not prepared to speculate about motivation.<ref name=\"Pre\">{{cite news |work=[[CNN]] |date=August 4, 2019 |first1=Sarah |last1=Aarthun |first2=Emanuella |last2=Grinberg |title= What we know about the shooting in Dayton, Ohio |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/08/04/us/dayton-ohio-shooting-what-we-know/index.html}}</ref><ref name=\"BookbankShooting\">{{cite news |last1=Bookbank |first1=Sarah |title=Dayton police: 'Not close enough at all' to determine a motive in Oregon District shooting |url=https://www.cincinnati.com/story/news/crime/crime-and-courts/2019/08/05/dayton-shooting-oregon-district/1917620001/ |accessdate=August 5, 2019 |work=Cincinnati Enquirer |date=August 1, 2019}}</ref> On August 5, Dayton Police Chief Richard Biehl stated that: \"We have a lot of evidence still to go through...based on where we're at now, we are not seeing any indication of race being a motive.\"<ref name=\"LiMass\">{{cite news |last1=Li |first1=David K. |title=Dayton Police still don't know whether gunman targeted sister in mass shooting |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/dayton-police-still-don-t-know-if-gunman-targeted-sister-n1039236 |accessdate=August 5, 2019 |publisher=NBC News |date=August 5, 2019}}</ref> Investigators are divided and have not determined whether he shot his sibling deliberately.<ref name=\"LiMass\"/> A federal law enforcement official said that they were looking at whether the suspect was associated with [[incel]] groups.<ref name=\"RRSmith\">{{cite news |first1=Mitch |last1=Smith |first2=Rick |last2=Rojas |first3=Campbell |last3=Robertson |title=Mass Shootings Updates: The Dayton gunman appeared to be 'exploring violent ideologies,' the F.B.I. said. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/06/us/mass-shootings.html |accessdate=August 6, 2019 |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=August 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe suspect had additional ammunition magazines with him, and was wearing [[body armor]], a mask and hearing protection during the attack.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/08/04/us/dayton-ohio-active-shooter/index.html |title=The Dayton shooter wore a mask, bulletproof vest and hearing protection as he opened fire, police chief says |date=August 5, 2019 |publisher=[[CNN]] |first1=Jay |last1=Croft |first2=Darran |last2=Simon |access-date=August 5, 2019}}</ref> He ordered the firearm used in the shooting online from Texas, and the firearm was transferred to a local firearms dealer in Ohio, where he picked it up.<ref name=\"CNN-WhatWeKnow\"/> The firearm used was \"modified in essence to function like a rifle\", according to the Dayton Police; photos released by the Dayton Police show an [[AR-15 style rifle|AR-15 style firearm]] with a pistol brace.<ref name=Loophole>{{cite news |url=https://www.cincinnati.com/story/news/crime/crime-and-courts/2019/08/05/dayton-shooter-used-gun-may-have-exploited-atf-loophole/1920506001/ |title=Dayton shooter used a gun that may have exploited an ATF loophole |first=Cameron |last=Knight |website=[[The Cincinnati Enquirer]] |date=August 5, 2019 |accessdate=August 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn August 15, the Montgomery County Coroner announced that Betts had cocaine, alcohol and [[Xanax]] in his system, and had a [[vape pen]] and a baggie containing cocaine in one of his pockets.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coroner: 2 victims of Dayton mass shooting struck by rounds from shooter and police |url=https://www.cincinnati.com/story/news/2019/08/15/coroner-release-more-autopsy-information-dayton-shooting/2018778001 |agency=Montgomery County Coroner}}</ref>\n\n== Aftermath ==\n[[File:Bullet hole after the 2019 Dayton shooting (48464806611).jpg|thumb|right|Bullet holes in a window a day after the shooting]]\nMembers of the Southwest Ohio Critical Incident Stress Management Team met with police who had responded to the scene to help them process the situation. The team includes mental health professionals, police officers, firefighters, medics, and chaplains.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.journal-news.com/news/dayton-shooting-hood-survivor-helps-officers-deal-with-stress-carnage/ZNQgfaXFMlah1JCalKXVZL/|title=Dayton shooting: Ft. Hood survivor helps officers deal with stress of 'carnage'|last=Stewart|first=Chris |website=journal-news|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref>\n\nThe local [[blood bank]] asked for more donations following the shooting, and various companies promoted donation drives.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dayton.com/news/local/dayton-shooting-how-help-our-neighbors/dP6vIy8GAzuKBTm5NsFhMJ/|title=Dayton shooting: How to help our neighbors|first1=Lisa|last1=Powell|first2=Mark|last2=Fisher|website=dayton.com|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref> Local leaders and community members held a vigil on East 5th Street on August 4, where ten doves were released, one each for each dead victim and one for the wounded.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whio.com/news/local/dayton-shooting-candlelight-vigil-free-parking-rta-bus-rides/VNhsxyL7TMP3wt4h6F18PN/|title=Dayton shooting: People fill Oregon District for vigil|last=Filby|first=Max|date=August 4, 2019|website=whio.com|access-date=2019-08-06}}</ref>\n\n==Reactions==\n=== Domestic ===\n[[File:Note at Ned Peppers Bar after 2019 Dayton shooting.jpg|thumb|right|Note left at the entrance of Ned Peppers Bar the day after the shooting]]\nFollowing the shooting, Ned Peppers Bar posted a message on [[Instagram]] reading: \"All of our staff is safe and our hearts go out to everyone involved as we gather information.\"<ref>\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/us/at-least-10-may-be-dead-in-dayton-ohio-gunfire-reports|title=At least 10 may be dead in Dayton, Ohio, gunfire: reports|last=Calicchio|first=Dom|date=August 4, 2019|website=|publisher=[[Fox News]]|accessdate=August 4, 2019}}\n*{{cite news |author=Ned Peppers |publisher=[[Instagram]] |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B0u5Fu6jboI/ |date=August 4, 2019 |access-date=August 4, 2019 |title=all of our staff is safe and our hearts go out to everyone involved as we gather information}}</ref>\n\n[[File:President Trump Delivers Remarks 2019-08-05.webm|thumb|right|Trump delivers statement on August 5, 2019.]]\n[[President of the United States|President]] Donald Trump tweeted, \"God bless the people of El Paso Texas. God bless the people of Dayton, Ohio.\"<ref name=\"dayton\">{{cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/us/live-news/ohio-shooting/index.html|title=Mass shooting in Dayton, Ohio|first=Ivanna|last=Kottasova|date=August 4, 2019|publisher=CNN|accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref> In a later statement, he ordered that, following both shootings, all public U.S. flags be flown at [[half-staff]] until sunset on August 8.<ref name=bbclive>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/live/49227583|title=Two US mass shootings in 24 hours|work=BBC News|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref> Regarding mass shootings, he said, \"[[Donald Trump Administration|We]] have done much more than most administrations. We've actually done a lot. But perhaps more has to be done.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=LeMire |first1=Jonathan |title=Trump tweets, stays out of sight for hours after shootings |url=https://apnews.com/6d324c661d5f4a748c0990c8444efdb3 |agency=[[Associated Press]] |accessdate=August 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\nMayor Nan Whaley thanked the officers for a quick response, saying that it certainly prevented more deaths. She also spoke of how hard the day would be for the city and the families affected.<ref name=\"BBC\" /> Ohio Senator [[Rob Portman]] and Governor [[Mike DeWine]] offered their condolences.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Talmazan |first1=Yuliya |last2=Radnofsky |first2=Caroline |last3=Madani |first3=Doha |title=Shooting in Dayton, Ohio, kills at least 9 people and injures 27; suspect also dead |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/police-investigate-active-shooter-incident-dayton-ohio-n1039046 |publisher=NBC News|accessdate=August 5, 2019 |date=August 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\nSenator [[Sherrod Brown]], a Democrat representing Ohio, said \"[[Thoughts and prayers]] are not enough. We must act.\" He urged Senate Majority Leader [[Mitch McConnell]], a Republican, to start a [[United States Senate]] session on August 5 to \"vote on gun-safety laws\". Senate Minority Leader, [[Chuck Schumer]], a Democrat, made a similar call to action. He referenced H.R.8, the Bipartisan Background Checks Act of 2019 that had passed the [[United States House of Representatives]] earlier in February, saying the Senate should also pass this. Representative [[Ted Lieu]], a Democrat, asserted that McConnell was \"blocking\" the bipartisan proposal on \"common sense gun safety legislation\" from being voted on in the Senate.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clark |first1=Dartunorro |title=Democrats pressure Mitch McConnell to cancel Senate recess for gun control vote |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/politics-news/democrats-pressure-mitch-mcconnell-cancel-senate-recess-gun-control-vote-n1039086 |publisher=[[NBC News]] |accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Ohio House of Representatives]] member [[Candice Keller]] posted an essay on her personal Facebook page, blaming the shooting on several factors including [[recreational marijuana]] and the breakdown of the [[Nuclear family|traditional family]] (due to causes including transgender rights).<ref>\n*{{Cite news |last1=Bischoff |first1=Laura |url=https://www.daytondailynews.com/news/local/dayton-shooting-due-family-breakdown-gay-marriage-video-games-state-lawmaker-says/jf8XNJPSfKFl13yggzTFgM/ |title=Dayton shooting due to family breakdown, gay marriage, video games, state lawmaker says |work=[[Dayton Daily News]] |date=August 4, 2019 |accessdate=August 5, 2019}}\n*{{cite news |last1=Horton |first1=Alex |title=Ohio Republican blames mass shootings on 'drag queen advocates,' Colin Kaepernick and Obama |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2019/08/05/ohio-republican-blames-mass-shootings-drag-queen-advocates-colin-kaepernick-obama/ |website=[[The Washington Post]] |accessdate=August 8, 2019 |date=August 5, 2019}}</ref> Her statement was criticized by [[Cincinnati City Council]] member [[Chris Seelbach (politician)|Chris Seelbach]], [[Butler County, Ohio|Butler County]] Sheriff Richard K. Jones, and [[Ohio Republican Party]] chairwoman [[Jane Timken]] (who called on her to resign).<ref>\n*{{cite news |last1=Wartman |first1=Scott |last2=Balmert |first2=Jessie |title=Southwest Ohio politician blames shootings on 'drag queen advocates' and open borders |url=https://www.cincinnati.com/story/news/politics/2019/08/04/ohio-shooting-state-rep-blames-shootings-drag-queen-advocates-and-open-borders/1918106001/ |work=[[Cincinnati Enquirer]] |date=August 4, 2019 |accessdate=August 5, 2019}}\n*{{cite news |last1=Balmert |first1=Jessie |title=Republican lawmaker asked to resign after 'shocking' Facebook post blamed Dayton shooting on 'drag queen advocates' |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2019/08/06/ohio-gop-leader-tells-lawmaker-resign-over-dayton-shooting-post/1930213001/ |accessdate=August 8, 2019 |work=[[USA Today]] |date=August 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the [[2019 El Paso shooting|El Paso shooting]], which occurred 13 hours prior,<ref name=\"auto\"/> multiple Democratic [[2020 United States presidential election|2020 presidential election]] candidates called for political action to eliminate [[gun violence in the United States]]; they included [[Cory Booker]],<ref name=\"PoliticoReactions\">{{cite news |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2019/08/03/el-paso-shooting-orourke-1445509 |title='The numbers are going up': Unfolding El Paso massacre stuns Dem presidential forum |last1=Siders |first1=David |last2=Vasquez |first2=Christian |work=[[Politico]] |accessdate=August 3, 2019}}</ref> [[Pete Buttigieg]],<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.latimes.com/politics/story/2019-08-03/democratic-candidates-el-paso-shooting-beto-orourke |title='Keep that ... on the battlefield': Beto O'Rourke condemns access to assault weapons after El Paso shooting |last1=Montero |first1=David |last2=Finnegan |first2=Michael |website=[[Los Angeles Times]] |accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref> [[Tim Ryan (Ohio politician)|Tim Ryan]],<ref>{{citation |newspaper=[[The Courier-Journal]] |location=Louisville, Kentucky |date=August 8, 2019 |accessdate=August 8, 2019 |first=Sarah |last=Ladd |url=https://www.courier-journal.com/story/news/local/2019/08/07/tim-ryan-moms-demand-action-rally-against-mcconnell-louisville/1948668001/ |title=Tim Ryan caravan coming to Mitch McConnell's hometown after Dayton, El Paso mass shootings}}</ref> [[Bernie Sanders]],<ref name=\"HillReactions\">{{cite news |url=https://thehill.com/homenews/campaign/456067-2020-dems-call-for-action-after-el-paso-shooting |title=2020 Dems call for action after El Paso shooting |last1=Frazin |first1=Rachel |website=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]] |accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref> [[Elizabeth Warren]],<ref name=\"HillReactions\" /> and [[Andrew Yang]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.msnbc.com/msnbc/watch/andrew-yang-discusses-gun-reform-in-response-to-el-paso-dayton-shootings-65300037753 |title=Andrew Yang discusses gun reform in response to El Paso, Dayton shootings |publisher=[[MSNBC]] |access-date=August 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nTrump visited El Paso and Dayton on August 7. In Dayton, he spoke to hospitalized victims, medical staff, and first responders. The White House published photos and videos of his trip, some of which showed him posing, smiling, and giving [[thumbs up]] gestures with his hosts.<ref>\n*{{cite news |last1=Parker |first1=Ashley |last2=Rucker |first2=Philip |last3=Johnson |first3=Jenna |last4=Sonmez |first4=Felicia |title=Trump attacks local leaders as he visits two cities grieving from mass shootings |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/trump-lashes-out-at-beto-orourke-and-the-media-ahead-of-visits-to-el-paso-and-dayton/2019/08/07/b0aa8afc-b8fb-11e9-b3b4-2bb69e8c4e39_story.html |website=[[The Washington Post]] |accessdate=August 9, 2019 |date=August 8, 2019}}\n*{{cite news |title=Self-promotion: Trump boasts of rally crowd size during hospital visit to console Texas massacre survivors |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2019/08/09/world/politics-diplomacy-world/self-promotion-trump-boasts-rally-crowd-size-hospital-visit-console-texas-massacre-survivors/ |website=[[Agence France Presse]] and [[Jiji Press]] |accessdate=August 9, 2019 |date=August 9, 2019}}</ref> He told reporters, \"We had an amazing day. The love, the respect for the office of the presidency {{ndash}} I wish you could have been in there to see it.\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Crowley |first1=Michael |last2=Haberman |first2=Maggie |last3=Smith |first3=Mitch |last4=Shear |first4=Michael |title=Trump Uses a Day of Healing to Deepen the Nation's Divisions |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/07/us/politics/trump-el-paso-dayton-shootings.html |website=[[The New York Times]] |accessdate=August 9, 2019 |date=August 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== International ===\nThe incident was mentioned by [[Pope Francis]] during a speech in [[St. Peter's Square]] on August 4, in which he condemned attacks on defenseless people and said he was spiritually close to the victims, the wounded and the families affected by the attacks that had \"bloodied [[2019 El Paso shooting|Texas]], [[Gilroy Garlic Festival shooting|California]], and Ohio\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-texas-shooting-pope-idUSKCN1UU0BC|title=Pope condemns spate of U.S. gun violence, prays for victims|date=2019-08-04|agency=Reuters|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref>\n\nIn response to the shooting, the [[Consulate General of Japan in Detroit]] issued a notice stating that no Asians had been injured and that \"Japanese residents should be aware of the potential for gunfire incidents everywhere in the United States, a [[gun culture in the United States|gun society]], and continue to pay close attention to safety measures.\"<ref name=\"nations\">{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2019/08/07/748971210/after-mass-shootings-other-nations-issue-caution-about-gun-society-in-u-s|first1=Scott|last1=Neuman|title=After Mass Shootings, Other Nations Issue Caution about 'Gun Society' in US|publisher=NPR|date=August 7, 2019|accessdate=August 7, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.anzen.mofa.go.jp/od/ryojiMailDetail.html?keyCd=74322|title=About Shooting Incidents in Dayton, Ohio|publisher=Consulate General of Japan in Detroit|date=August 4, 2019}}</ref> At least two other nations \u2013 [[Uruguay]] and [[Venezuela]] \u2014 issued similar travel warnings, with Uruguay's foreign ministry issuing a statement warning its citizens traveling in the U.S. \"to take precautions against growing indiscriminate violence, mostly for [[hate crime]]s, including [[racism]] and [[discrimination]],\" and Venezuela cautioning its citizens to postpone travel to the U.S. or to take precautions \"given the proliferation of acts of violence and crimes of indiscriminate hatred.\"<ref name=\"nations\"/>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Law|United States}}\n*[[List of mass shootings in the United States]]\n*[[Mass shootings in the United States]]\n*[[Gun violence in the United States]]\n\n{{-}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/05/us/dayton-shooting-victims.html ''The New York Times'' list of victims fatally shot]\n* {{Commons-inline}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dayton shooting, 2019}}\n[[Category:2019 in Ohio]]\n[[Category:2019 mass shootings in the United States]]\n[[Category:2010s crimes in Ohio]]\n[[Category:Attacks on bars]]\n[[Category:August 2019 crimes in the United States]]\n[[Category:Deaths by firearm in Ohio]]\n[[Category:History of Dayton, Ohio|2019 shooting]]\n[[Category:Mass murder in 2019]]\n[[Category:Mass murder in the United States]]\n[[Category:Mass shootings in Ohio]]\n[[Category:Mass shootings in the United States]]\n[[Category:Murder in Ohio]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Mass shooting in Dayton, Ohio, United States of America}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use American English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox civilian attack\n| title         = Dayton bar shooting\n| partof        = \n| image         = Ned_Peppers_Bar_after_2019_Dayton_shooting.jpg\n| image_size    = \n| image_upright = 1.25\n| alt           = \n| caption       = Ned Peppers Bar the day after the shooting\n| map           = Map of 2019 Dayton Shooting.svg\n| map_size      = \n| map_alt       = \n| map_caption   = Map of the events of the shooting within the [[Oregon Historic District]]\n| location      = 419 East 5th Street<br />[[Dayton, Ohio]], United States\n| target        = \n| coordinates   = {{coord|39.7572|-84.1843|type:event_region:US-OH|display=it}}\n| date          = {{Start date|2019|8|4}}\n| time          = 1:05 a.m.\n| timezone      = [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]] [[UTC\u221204:00]]\n| type          = [[Mass shooting]]\n| weapons       = AR-15 style pistol using [[.223 Remington]] with a 100-round [[drum magazine]]<ref name=\"WSJ20190805\" /><ref name=Loophole/>\n| fatalities    = 10 (including the perpetrator)\n| injuries      = 27 (17 from gunfire)<ref name=\"AP17\" /><ref name=DPD.190815/>\n| victims       = <!-- or | victim = -->\n| assailants    = \n| perp          = Connor Stephen Betts\n| numparts      = <!-- or | numpart = -->\n| dfens         = <!-- or | dfen = -->\n| website       = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| module        = \n}}\n\nOn August 4, 2019, Connor Stephen Betts, 24, fatally shot nine people and wounded 17 others near the entrance of the Ned Peppers Bar in [[Dayton, Ohio]].<ref name=\"AP17\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcbayarea.com/news/national-international/Dayton-Gunman-Deadly-Mass-Shooting-539291401.html|title=Ohio Shooter Hit 26 People in Half a Minute|date=13 August 2019|publisher=[[Associated Press]]}}</ref> Betts was fatally shot by responding police officers 32 seconds after his first shot.<ref name=\"Sec\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.wlwt.com/article/police-gunman-s-sister-among-9-killed-in-dayton-mass-shooting/28599430|quote=According to Dayton Police Chief Richard Biehl, officers engaged the suspect within 20 seconds of hearing shots fired. Thirty seconds after the gunman began shooting, he was shot and killed by first responders, Biehl said.|title=Police: Gunman's sister among 9 killed in Dayton mass shooting|publisher=WLWT 5|date=August 4, 2019|accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref> An additional ten persons were injured by other causes, bringing the total number of wounded to 27.<ref name=\"AP17\" />\n\nA search of the shooter's home found evidence that showed an interest in violence and [[mass shootings]] and he had expressed a desire to commit one. Despite describing himself as a [[leftist]] and voicing his support for [[Antifa (United States)|Antifa]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/us/live-news/el-paso-dayton-shootings-august-2019/h_c3fe4a1d2b04da849422f817647227ab |title=The Dayton shooter had an extreme left Twitter feed |first1=Paul |last1=Murphy |first2=Konstantin |last2=Toropin |date=2019-08-05 |website=[[CNN]] |access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref> a preliminary assessment did not indicate that Betts had a racial or political motive.<ref name=\"Pre\"/> The attack occurred just 13 hours after an [[2019 El Paso shooting|earlier mass shooting in El Paso, Texas]].<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/aug/04/mass-shootings-el-paso-texas-dayton-ohio|title=Thirty dead in 13 hours: US reckons with back-to-back mass shootings|first1=Sam Levin Oliver|last1=Laughland|first2=Joanna Walters in New|last2=York|date=August 5, 2019|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref>\n\n==Attack==\nTwo hours before the attack, the gunman was seen entering a bar with his sibling<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/amberjamieson/dayton-shooting-victims|title=The Victims Of The Dayton Mass Shooting Include The Gunman\u2019s Brother And 8 Others|publisher=[[BuzzFeed News]]|date=August 4, 2019|access-date=August 12, 2019}}</ref> and a friend in the downtown [[Oregon Historic District]] of Dayton. At about 12:13&nbsp;a.m., he split from the two and was recorded leaving the bar.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/08/06/us/surveillance-video-connor-betts-in-bar/index.html |title=Exclusive video shows Dayton gunman Connor Betts in bar in the hours before shooting |first1=Noah |last1=Gray |first2=Curt |last2=Devine |first3=Patricia |last3=DiCarlo |first4=Mark |last4=Morales |website=[[CNN]] |date=August 6, 2019 |accessdate=August 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAt 1:05&nbsp;a.m., eyewitnesses reported that a man opened fire at the entrance of Ned Peppers Bar in the Oregon Historic District.<ref name=\"Heavy\">{{Cite web|url=https://heavy.com/news/2019/08/dayton-ohio-active-shooter-shooting/|title=Dayton Mass Shooting: Multiple Dead at Ned Peppers Bar in Ohio|publisher=Heavy.com|date=August 4, 2019|accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref> He was carrying a firearm that included part of a [[Semi-automatic pistol|semi-automatic]] AM-15 (based on the [[AR-15 style rifle|AR-15)]]<ref name=\"WSJ20190805\">{{cite news |last1=Kesling |first1=Ben |title=Dayton Shooter Used AR-15 Pistol, Smaller Version of Popular Rifle |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/dayton-shooter-used-ar-15-pistol-smaller-version-of-popular-rifle-11565045046 |accessdate=August 5, 2019 |work=The Wall Street Journal |url-access=limited |date=August 5, 2019}}</ref><ref name=PohlmanWKRC>{{cite news |url=https://local12.com/news/duane-is-that-right/key-section-of-weapon-used-in-dayton-mass-shooting-manufactured-in-tri-state |title=Key section of weapon used in Dayton mass shooting manufactured in Tri-State |first=Duane |last=Pohlman |website=local12.com |publisher=[[WKRC-TV]] |date=August 5, 2019 |accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref> in a [[pistol]] configuration with a shortened [[Barrel (firearm)|barrel]], chambered in [[.223 Remington|.223 caliber]] ammunition and equipped with a 100-round [[drum magazine]].<ref name=Loophole/><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2019/08/05/us/gun-laws-el-paso-dayton-shootings.html |title=How State Laws Allowed Military-Style Guns Used in Dayton and El Paso Shootings |first1=Larry |last1=Buchanan |first2=K.K. Rebecca |last2=Lai |website=[[The New York Times]] |url-access=limited |date=August 5, 2019 |accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref> He fired 41 rounds into the crowd in less than 30 seconds, fatally shooting nine people.<ref name=\"obession\" /><ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|url=https://www.wmra.org/post/9-killed-least-16-injured-shooting-dayton-ohio#stream/0|title=9 Killed, 26 Injured In Shooting In Dayton, Ohio|date=August 4, 2019|publisher=[[WMRA]]|access-date=August 4, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"CNN-WhatWeKnow\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/us/live-news/ohio-shooting/index.html|title=What we know about the Dayton shooting|website=|publisher=CNN|last=Kottasova|first=Ivana|date=August 4, 2019|access-date=August 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAccording to Dayton Police Chief Richard Biehl, 20 seconds after the shooting began,<ref name=\"Sec\"/> law enforcement officers already on the scene engaged the gunman.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/us/live-news/ohio-shooting/index.html|title=Mass shooting in Dayton, Ohio|publisher=[[CNN]]|date=August 4, 2019|access-date=August 4, 2019}}</ref> Within 32 seconds after the first shots were fired,<ref name=\"AP17\"/> the gunman was shot dead.<ref name=\"BBC\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-49224816|title=Dayton shooting: Nine confirmed killed, gunman also dead|date=2019-08-04|access-date=2019-08-04|publisher=[[BBC]]}}</ref> An autopsy report released on December 6, 2019, showed that Betts was hit with 30 rounds.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cincinnati.com/story/news/2019/12/06/dayton-shooters-autopsy-lists-30-gunshot-wounds/4357662002/|title=Autopsy reveals Dayton shooter was hit with 30 rounds in 32 seconds|first=Madeline|last=Mitchell|website=Cincinnati.com}}</ref> Local police evacuated many nearby night venues, and warned Dayton residents to stay away from the Oregon Historic District.<ref name=\"BBC\" />\n\n==Victims==\n[[File:Vigil for Shooting Victims, Dayton (OH)05-(1b) (48464805991).jpg|thumb|Vigil for the victims, August 5, 2019]]\n[[Miami Valley Hospital]] received 16 victims from the shooting, of which five were admitted, one in critical condition. [[Kettering Health Network]], comprising nine hospitals in the area, received nine victims, with three in serious condition and three in fair condition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/active-shooter-incident-investigated-dayton-ohio-police/story?id=64763090|title=At least 9 dead, 26 injured in mass shooting in downtown Dayton; suspect identified|last=Osborne|first=Mark|publisher=ABC News|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref> By 10:00&nbsp;a.m. on the same day, 15 of 27 hospitalized people had been discharged.<ref name=\"BBC\" />\nOf the injured, 17 were shot.\n\nPolice reported that all the fatalities occurred outside the bar on East 5th Street,<ref name=\"BBC\" /> and that the shooter's 22-year-old sibling was among those killed.<ref>\n*{{Cite news |url=https://heavy.com/news/2019/08/connor-betts-sister-megan-betts/ |title=Megan Betts, Connor Betts' Sister, Found Dead |first=Paul |last=Farrell |date=August 4, 2019 |accessdate=August 4, 2019 |publisher=[[Heavy.com]]}}\n*{{cite news |last1=Feldman |first1=Kate |title=Nine dead, at least 26 injured in Dayton, Ohio, after 24-year-old gunman in body armor opens fire |url=https://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/ny-dayton-ohio-mass-shooting-20190804-pmcnqkoid5defoiy6hhngi2pfm-story.html |accessdate=August 4, 2019 |work=Daily News |date=August 4, 2019}}\n*{{cite news |url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/jordan-cofer-trans-victim-dayton-mass-shooting/amp |title=Remembering Jordan Cofer, Trans Victim of the Dayton Mass Shooting |work=[[Teen Vogue]] |first=Sarah Emily |last=Baum |date=August 12, 2019 |access-date=August 13, 2019}}</ref> Investigators are trying to determine if the gunman intentionally or accidentally killed his sibling, who was among the first victims.<ref>{{cite news |work=[[USA Today]] |date=August 5, 2019 |first=Anne |last=Saker |title=Dayton shooting: Gunman killed his sister, but was the 'sororicide' intentional? |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2019/08/05/dayton-shooting-too-early-tell-reasons-connor-betts-killed-sister/1928195001/}}</ref>\n\nThe nine dead include five males and four females, six black and three white. Four of the dead were in their 20s, four more were in their 30s, and one was 57.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/04/us/dayton-ohio-shooting.html |work=[[The New York Times]] |title=Dayton, Ohio, Shooting: Victims Identified; Live Updates |date=August 4, 2019 |first1=Timothy |last1=Williams |first2=Farah |last2=Stockman |access-date=August 4, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bostonherald.com/2019/08/04/the-latest-9-killed-at-least-16-hurt-in-ohio-shooting/ |work=[[Boston Herald]] |title=The Latest: Neighbors recall Ohio shooter being 'good kid' |date=August 4, 2019 |access-date=August 4, 2019}}</ref> Two of the victims who died were also shot by police.<ref name=\"AP17\"/><ref name=DPD.190815>{{cite tweet |user=DaytonPolice |number=1162080211229429762 |date=August 15, 2019 |title=Dr. Harshbarger - There were two victims who were hit additionally as a result of the law enforcement response.}}</ref><ref>\n*{{cite news|url=https://www.wcpo.com/news/national/dayton-shooting-police-still-trying-to-determine-motive-say-14-injured-suffered-gunshot-wounds|title=Dayton shooting: Police still trying to determine motive, say 14 injured suffered gunshot wounds|publisher=[[WCPO 9]]|date=August 5, 2019|access-date=August 6, 2019}}\n*{{cite tweet |user=DaytonPolice |number=1161355791275831298 |date=August 13, 2019 |title=Chief Biehl: We had 9 killed by gunshot wounds and 17 others injured by gunshots.}}</ref> An autopsy showed that a woman who was shot by Betts was already bleeding from a fatal gunshot wound when she was struck by two bullets which were fired by police. Had she not been suffering from fatal injuries, one of the bullets which were fired by police would have been lethal. The second victim was shot by Betts multiple times and sustained a superficial gunshot wound from police. As a result of those findings, Montgomery County Coroner Dr. Kent Harshbarger ruled that the deaths were caused by Betts and were not the result of police gunfire.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cincinnati.com/story/news/2019/08/15/coroner-release-more-autopsy-information-dayton-shooting/2018778001/|title=Coroner: 2 victims of Dayton mass shooting struck by rounds from shooter and police|first1=Sarah|last1=Brookbank|first2=Kevin|last2=Grasha|first3=Chris|last3=Mayhew|website=Cincinnati.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wcpo.com/news/mass-shooting/none-of-dayton-victims-killed-by-police-fire-coroner-says|title=None of nine Dayton victims killed by police fire, coroner says|date=August 15, 2019|website=WCPO}}</ref>\n\n==Perpetrator==\nSoon after the attack, police identified the gunman as '''Connor Stephen Betts''',<!--The name of the perpetrator is in BOLD to indicate that [[Connor Stephen Betts]] is a redirect to the article, and thus supports the principle of least astonishment when a redirected reader arrives. See MOS:BOLD. Do not remove, please.--><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aol.com/article/news/2019/08/14/dayton-mass-shooter-connor-betts-obituary/23793379/|title=Family of Dayton mass shooter Connor Betts remembers him as 'funny,' 'intelligent' in obituary|last=Staff|first=A. O. L.|website=AOL.com|language=en|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref> a 24-year-old who lived in [[Bellbrook, Ohio]].<ref name=\"BBC\" /><ref>\n*{{cite news |title=Connor Betts' Family: 5 Fast Facts You Need to Know |url=https://heavy.com/news/2019/08/connor-betts-family-parents-mother-father/ |accessdate=10 August 2019 |agency=Heavy |date=10 August 2019}}\n*{{cite news|url=https://abc7chicago.com/connor-stephen-betts-idd-as-dayton-suspected-shooter-sources/5442328/|title=Connor Stephen Betts identified as Dayton suspected shooter; Suspect's sister found dead, sources say|date=August 4, 2019|publisher=ABC-7|location=Chicago|accessdate=August 4, 2019}}\n*{{cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/live-news/dayton-ohio-shooting-suspect-connor-betts-9-killed-mass-shooting-today-2019-08-04-live-updates/|title=9 killed in Dayton, Ohio, in second U.S. mass shooting in 24 hours|date=August 4, 2019|accessdate=August 4, 2019|publisher=CBS News|agency=Associated Press}}</ref>  According to police, he had minor traffic offenses on his record.<ref name=\"Cincinnati\" /><ref>\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/connor-betts-24-idd-as-dayton-ohio-shooter|title=Dayton Shooter Murdered Sister in Attack, Officials Say|last1=Nadeau|first1=Barbie Latza|last2=Daly|first2=Michael|date=August 4, 2019|via=thedailybeast.com}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/08/05/us/connor-betts-dayton-shooting-profile/index.html|title=Classmates say Dayton gunman had a 'hit list' in high school|last1=Murphy|first1=Paul P.|last2=Ash|first2=Audrey|publisher=CNN|last3=Crespo|first3=Gisela}}</ref>\n\nBetts made online references about [[Satan]] and described himself as a leftist and [[Antifa (United States)|Antifa]] sympathizer.<ref name=\"Satan\">{{cite web|url=https://www.snopes.com/fact-check/dayton-shooter-warren/|title=Was Dayton Mass Shooter a Self-Described 'Pro-Satan Leftist Who Supported Elizabeth Warren'?|website=[[Snopes]]|date=August 5, 2019|accessdate=August 5, 2019|first=Alex|last=Kasprak}}</ref><ref name=\"heavy5\">{{cite web |url=https://heavy.com/news/2019/08/connor-betts-twitter-politics-social-media/ |title=Connor Betts: Twitter Posts on Being a Leftist, Guns |publisher=[[Heavy.com]] |last=McBride |first=Jessica |date=August 4, 2019 |accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"MurphyFeed\">{{cite news |last1=Murphy |first1=Paul P. |last2=Toropin |first2=Konstantin |last3=Griffin |first3=Drew |last4=Bronstein |first4=Scott |title=Dayton shooter appeared to have leftist Twitter feed |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/08/05/us/connor-betts-dayton-shooting-profile/index.html |accessdate=August 6, 2019 |publisher=CNN |date=August 5, 2019}}</ref>  In the hours before he opened fire in Dayton, he \"liked\" a post in favor of [[Gun control in the United States|gun control]], and several concerning the El Paso shooting, including a tweet that called the El Paso shooter a \"terrorist\" and a \"[[white supremacist]].\"<ref name=\"MurphyFeed\" /> On August 10, [[ABC News]] quoted officials as stating that the gunman had [[misogynist]] views which were much more extreme than his political views.<ref name=\"exmis\">{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/alleged-dayton-gunman-connor-betts-showed-signs-misogyny/story?id=64826324|title=Alleged Dayton gunman showed signs of misogyny, mirroring a grim pattern for shooters|last1=Svokos|first1=Alexandra|website=[[ABC News]]|accessdate=August 14, 2019}}</ref> Betts was also known to have been in support of presidential candidates [[Elizabeth Warren]] and [[Bernie Sanders]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2019/08/07/dayton-shooting-what-do-we-know-connor-betts-politics/1943289001/|title=Dayton shooting: What we know about the gunman's politics|last=Knight|first=Keith BieryGolick and Cameron|website=USA TODAY|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/us/live-news/el-paso-dayton-shootings-august-2019/h_c3fe4a1d2b04da849422f817647227ab|title=The Dayton shooter had an extreme left Twitter feed|author1=Meg Wagner |author2=Elise Hammond |author3=Mike Hayes |author4=Veronica Rocha|date=2019-08-05|website=CNN|language=en|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref>\n\nTwo former high school classmates said Betts was suspended from [[Bellbrook High School]] after he made lists of other students he wanted to kill and rape.<ref name=\"Kill-list\">{{cite news |last1=Biesecker |first1=Michael |last2=Carr Smyth |first2=Julie |title=Classmates: Ohio shooter kept a 'hit list' and a 'rape list' |url=https://news.yahoo.com/classmates-ohio-shooter-kept-hit-033305480.html |accessdate=August 5, 2019 |agency=Associated Press |date=August 5, 2019}}</ref> The \"hit list\" was discovered in early 2012 and resulted in a police investigation.<ref name=\"Kill-list\" /> He was previously bullied and had planned to shoot up the school, a classmate said.<ref name=Cincinnati>{{cite web |url=https://www.cincinnati.com/story/news/2019/08/04/dayton-shooting-what-we-know-gunman/1916121001/ |title=Dayton shooting: What we know about the gunman |work=[[Cincinnati Enquirer]] |date=August 4, 2019 |last1=Trombly |first1=Monroe |last2=Baldas |first2=Tresa |accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref> Over the past year, the gunman had performed live vocals for a [[pornogrind]] band called Menstrual Munchies, a genre which ''[[Vice News]]'' described as a \"misogynistic, male-dominated\" music scene, and [[Buzzfeed]] described as focused on gore, violence, and necrophilia, and known for its dark, satirical themes of sexual violence delivered for shock value.<ref>\n*{{cite news |work=[[BuzzFeed News]] |date=August 5, 2019 |first=Ellie |last=Hall |title=The Dayton Shooter Was The Lead Singer Of A \"Pornogrind\" Metal Band |url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/ellievhall/dayton-shooter-pornogrind-band}}\n*{{Cite news |title=Exclusive: Dayton Shooter Was in a \"Pornogrind\" Band That Released Songs About Raping and Killing Women |work=[[Vice News]] |date=August 5, 2019 |accessdate=August 5, 2019 |url=https://news.vice.com/en_us/article/j5yekp/exclusive-dayton-shooter-was-in-a-pornogrind-band-that-released-songs-about-raping-and-killing-women}}</ref> His high school girlfriend said he complained of visual and auditory [[hallucination]]s and [[psychosis]], and was afraid of developing [[schizophrenia]].<ref>\n*{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/police-chief-it-seems-to-defy-believability-that-dayton-shooter-would-kill-his-own-sister/2019/08/05/920a895c-b79e-11e9-b3b4-2bb69e8c4e39_story.html |title=Ex-girlfriend says Dayton shooter heard voices, talked about 'dark, evil things' |work=[[The Washington Post]] |date=August 5, 2019 |first1=Emily |last1=Davies |first2=Tim |last2=Craig |first3=Hannah |last3=Natanson |access-date=August 5, 2019}}\n*{{cite news |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=August 6, 2019 |agency=[[Associated Press]] |title='He trusted me': ex-girlfriend says Ohio gunman wrestled with dark thoughts |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2019/aug/06/he-trusted-me-ex-girlfriend-reveals-ohio-gunmans-darkest-thoughts}}</ref>\n\n== Investigation ==\nOn August 4, police and the [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] searched the shooter's home and found evidence that showed an interest in violence and mass shootings and that he had expressed a desire to commit a mass shooting.<ref name=\"obession\">{{cite news |last1=Murphy |first1=Paul |title=Dayton shooter had an obsession with violence and mass shootings, police say |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/08/05/us/connor-betts-dayton-shooting-profile/index.html |accessdate=31 August 2019 |publisher=CNN |date=August 7, 2019}}</ref> A preliminary assessment did not indicate the shooter had a racial or political motive.<ref name=\"Pre\" /> {{As of|2019|08|5|df=US}}, police investigators stated that the investigation is ongoing and that they are not prepared to speculate about motivation.<ref name=\"Pre\">{{cite news |work=[[CNN]] |date=August 4, 2019 |first1=Sarah |last1=Aarthun |first2=Emanuella |last2=Grinberg |title= What we know about the shooting in Dayton, Ohio |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/08/04/us/dayton-ohio-shooting-what-we-know/index.html}}</ref><ref name=\"BookbankShooting\">{{cite news |last1=Bookbank |first1=Sarah |title=Dayton police: 'Not close enough at all' to determine a motive in Oregon District shooting |url=https://www.cincinnati.com/story/news/crime/crime-and-courts/2019/08/05/dayton-shooting-oregon-district/1917620001/ |accessdate=August 5, 2019 |work=Cincinnati Enquirer |date=August 1, 2019}}</ref> On August 5, Dayton Police Chief Richard Biehl stated that: \"We have a lot of evidence still to go through...based on where we're at now, we are not seeing any indication of race being a motive.\"<ref name=\"LiMass\">{{cite news |last1=Li |first1=David K. |title=Dayton Police still don't know whether gunman targeted sister in mass shooting |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/dayton-police-still-don-t-know-if-gunman-targeted-sister-n1039236 |accessdate=August 5, 2019 |publisher=NBC News |date=August 5, 2019}}</ref> Investigators are divided and have not determined whether he shot his sibling deliberately.<ref name=\"LiMass\"/> A federal law enforcement official said that they were looking at whether the suspect was associated with [[incel]] groups.<ref name=\"RRSmith\">{{cite news |first1=Mitch |last1=Smith |first2=Rick |last2=Rojas |first3=Campbell |last3=Robertson |title=Mass Shootings Updates: The Dayton gunman appeared to be 'exploring violent ideologies,' the F.B.I. said. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/06/us/mass-shootings.html |accessdate=August 6, 2019 |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=August 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe suspect had additional ammunition magazines with him, and was wearing [[body armor]], a mask and hearing protection during the attack.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/08/04/us/dayton-ohio-active-shooter/index.html |title=The Dayton shooter wore a mask, bulletproof vest and hearing protection as he opened fire, police chief says |date=August 5, 2019 |publisher=[[CNN]] |first1=Jay |last1=Croft |first2=Darran |last2=Simon |access-date=August 5, 2019}}</ref> He ordered the firearm used in the shooting online from Texas, and the firearm was transferred to a local firearms dealer in Ohio, where he picked it up.<ref name=\"CNN-WhatWeKnow\"/> The firearm used was \"modified in essence to function like a rifle\", according to the Dayton Police; photos released by the Dayton Police show an [[AR-15 style rifle|AR-15 style firearm]] with a pistol brace.<ref name=Loophole>{{cite news |url=https://www.cincinnati.com/story/news/crime/crime-and-courts/2019/08/05/dayton-shooter-used-gun-may-have-exploited-atf-loophole/1920506001/ |title=Dayton shooter used a gun that may have exploited an ATF loophole |first=Cameron |last=Knight |website=[[The Cincinnati Enquirer]] |date=August 5, 2019 |accessdate=August 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn August 15, the Montgomery County Coroner announced that Betts had cocaine, alcohol and [[Xanax]] in his system, and had a [[vape pen]] and a baggie containing cocaine in one of his pockets.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coroner: 2 victims of Dayton mass shooting struck by rounds from shooter and police |url=https://www.cincinnati.com/story/news/2019/08/15/coroner-release-more-autopsy-information-dayton-shooting/2018778001 |agency=Montgomery County Coroner}}</ref>\n\n== Aftermath ==\n[[File:Bullet hole after the 2019 Dayton shooting (48464806611).jpg|thumb|right|Bullet holes in a window a day after the shooting]]\nMembers of the Southwest Ohio Critical Incident Stress Management Team met with police who had responded to the scene to help them process the situation. The team includes mental health professionals, police officers, firefighters, medics, and chaplains.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.journal-news.com/news/dayton-shooting-hood-survivor-helps-officers-deal-with-stress-carnage/ZNQgfaXFMlah1JCalKXVZL/|title=Dayton shooting: Ft. Hood survivor helps officers deal with stress of 'carnage'|last=Stewart|first=Chris |website=journal-news|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref>\n\nThe local [[blood bank]] asked for more donations following the shooting, and various companies promoted donation drives.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dayton.com/news/local/dayton-shooting-how-help-our-neighbors/dP6vIy8GAzuKBTm5NsFhMJ/|title=Dayton shooting: How to help our neighbors|first1=Lisa|last1=Powell|first2=Mark|last2=Fisher|website=dayton.com|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref> Local leaders and community members held a vigil on East 5th Street on August 4, where ten doves were released, one each for each dead victim and one for the wounded.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whio.com/news/local/dayton-shooting-candlelight-vigil-free-parking-rta-bus-rides/VNhsxyL7TMP3wt4h6F18PN/|title=Dayton shooting: People fill Oregon District for vigil|last=Filby|first=Max|date=August 4, 2019|website=whio.com|access-date=2019-08-06}}</ref>\n\n==Reactions==\n=== Domestic ===\n[[File:Note at Ned Peppers Bar after 2019 Dayton shooting.jpg|thumb|right|Note left at the entrance of Ned Peppers Bar the day after the shooting]]\nFollowing the shooting, Ned Peppers Bar posted a message on [[Instagram]] reading: \"All of our staff is safe and our hearts go out to everyone involved as we gather information.\"<ref>\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/us/at-least-10-may-be-dead-in-dayton-ohio-gunfire-reports|title=At least 10 may be dead in Dayton, Ohio, gunfire: reports|last=Calicchio|first=Dom|date=August 4, 2019|website=|publisher=[[Fox News]]|accessdate=August 4, 2019}}\n*{{cite news |author=Ned Peppers |publisher=[[Instagram]] |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B0u5Fu6jboI/ |date=August 4, 2019 |access-date=August 4, 2019 |title=all of our staff is safe and our hearts go out to everyone involved as we gather information}}</ref>\n\n[[File:President Trump Delivers Remarks 2019-08-05.webm|thumb|right|Trump delivers statement on August 5, 2019.]]\n[[President of the United States|President]] Donald Trump tweeted, \"God bless the people of El Paso Texas. God bless the people of Dayton, Ohio.\"<ref name=\"dayton\">{{cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/us/live-news/ohio-shooting/index.html|title=Mass shooting in Dayton, Ohio|first=Ivanna|last=Kottasova|date=August 4, 2019|publisher=CNN|accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref> In a later statement, he ordered that, following both shootings, all public U.S. flags be flown at [[half-staff]] until sunset on August 8.<ref name=bbclive>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/live/49227583|title=Two US mass shootings in 24 hours|work=BBC News|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref> Regarding mass shootings, he said, \"[[Donald Trump Administration|We]] have done much more than most administrations. We've actually done a lot. But perhaps more has to be done.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=LeMire |first1=Jonathan |title=Trump tweets, stays out of sight for hours after shootings |url=https://apnews.com/6d324c661d5f4a748c0990c8444efdb3 |agency=[[Associated Press]] |accessdate=August 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\nMayor Nan Whaley thanked the officers for a quick response, saying that it certainly prevented more deaths. She also spoke of how hard the day would be for the city and the families affected.<ref name=\"BBC\" /> Ohio Senator [[Rob Portman]] and Governor [[Mike DeWine]] offered their condolences.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Talmazan |first1=Yuliya |last2=Radnofsky |first2=Caroline |last3=Madani |first3=Doha |title=Shooting in Dayton, Ohio, kills at least 9 people and injures 27; suspect also dead |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/police-investigate-active-shooter-incident-dayton-ohio-n1039046 |publisher=NBC News|accessdate=August 5, 2019 |date=August 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\nSenator [[Sherrod Brown]], a Democrat representing Ohio, said \"[[Thoughts and prayers]] are not enough. We must act.\" He urged Senate Majority Leader [[Mitch McConnell]], a Republican, to start a [[United States Senate]] session on August 5 to \"vote on gun-safety laws\". Senate Minority Leader, [[Chuck Schumer]], a Democrat, made a similar call to action. He referenced H.R.8, the Bipartisan Background Checks Act of 2019 that had passed the [[United States House of Representatives]] earlier in February, saying the Senate should also pass this. Representative [[Ted Lieu]], a Democrat, asserted that McConnell was \"blocking\" the bipartisan proposal on \"common sense gun safety legislation\" from being voted on in the Senate.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clark |first1=Dartunorro |title=Democrats pressure Mitch McConnell to cancel Senate recess for gun control vote |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/politics-news/democrats-pressure-mitch-mcconnell-cancel-senate-recess-gun-control-vote-n1039086 |publisher=[[NBC News]] |accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Ohio House of Representatives]] member [[Candice Keller]] posted an essay on her personal Facebook page, blaming the shooting on several factors including [[recreational marijuana]] and the breakdown of the [[Nuclear family|traditional family]] (due to causes including transgender rights).<ref>\n*{{Cite news |last1=Bischoff |first1=Laura |url=https://www.daytondailynews.com/news/local/dayton-shooting-due-family-breakdown-gay-marriage-video-games-state-lawmaker-says/jf8XNJPSfKFl13yggzTFgM/ |title=Dayton shooting due to family breakdown, gay marriage, video games, state lawmaker says |work=[[Dayton Daily News]] |date=August 4, 2019 |accessdate=August 5, 2019}}\n*{{cite news |last1=Horton |first1=Alex |title=Ohio Republican blames mass shootings on 'drag queen advocates,' Colin Kaepernick and Obama |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2019/08/05/ohio-republican-blames-mass-shootings-drag-queen-advocates-colin-kaepernick-obama/ |website=[[The Washington Post]] |accessdate=August 8, 2019 |date=August 5, 2019}}</ref> Her statement was criticized by [[Cincinnati City Council]] member [[Chris Seelbach (politician)|Chris Seelbach]], [[Butler County, Ohio|Butler County]] Sheriff Richard K. Jones, and [[Ohio Republican Party]] chairwoman [[Jane Timken]] (who called on her to resign).<ref>\n*{{cite news |last1=Wartman |first1=Scott |last2=Balmert |first2=Jessie |title=Southwest Ohio politician blames shootings on 'drag queen advocates' and open borders |url=https://www.cincinnati.com/story/news/politics/2019/08/04/ohio-shooting-state-rep-blames-shootings-drag-queen-advocates-and-open-borders/1918106001/ |work=[[Cincinnati Enquirer]] |date=August 4, 2019 |accessdate=August 5, 2019}}\n*{{cite news |last1=Balmert |first1=Jessie |title=Republican lawmaker asked to resign after 'shocking' Facebook post blamed Dayton shooting on 'drag queen advocates' |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2019/08/06/ohio-gop-leader-tells-lawmaker-resign-over-dayton-shooting-post/1930213001/ |accessdate=August 8, 2019 |work=[[USA Today]] |date=August 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the [[2019 El Paso shooting|El Paso shooting]], which occurred 13 hours prior,<ref name=\"auto\"/> multiple Democratic [[2020 United States presidential election|2020 presidential election]] candidates called for political action to eliminate [[gun violence in the United States]]; they included [[Cory Booker]],<ref name=\"PoliticoReactions\">{{cite news |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2019/08/03/el-paso-shooting-orourke-1445509 |title='The numbers are going up': Unfolding El Paso massacre stuns Dem presidential forum |last1=Siders |first1=David |last2=Vasquez |first2=Christian |work=[[Politico]] |accessdate=August 3, 2019}}</ref> [[Pete Buttigieg]],<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.latimes.com/politics/story/2019-08-03/democratic-candidates-el-paso-shooting-beto-orourke |title='Keep that ... on the battlefield': Beto O'Rourke condemns access to assault weapons after El Paso shooting |last1=Montero |first1=David |last2=Finnegan |first2=Michael |website=[[Los Angeles Times]] |accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref> [[Tim Ryan (Ohio politician)|Tim Ryan]],<ref>{{citation |newspaper=[[The Courier-Journal]] |location=Louisville, Kentucky |date=August 8, 2019 |accessdate=August 8, 2019 |first=Sarah |last=Ladd |url=https://www.courier-journal.com/story/news/local/2019/08/07/tim-ryan-moms-demand-action-rally-against-mcconnell-louisville/1948668001/ |title=Tim Ryan caravan coming to Mitch McConnell's hometown after Dayton, El Paso mass shootings}}</ref> [[Bernie Sanders]],<ref name=\"HillReactions\">{{cite news |url=https://thehill.com/homenews/campaign/456067-2020-dems-call-for-action-after-el-paso-shooting |title=2020 Dems call for action after El Paso shooting |last1=Frazin |first1=Rachel |website=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]] |accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref> [[Elizabeth Warren]],<ref name=\"HillReactions\" /> and [[Andrew Yang]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.msnbc.com/msnbc/watch/andrew-yang-discusses-gun-reform-in-response-to-el-paso-dayton-shootings-65300037753 |title=Andrew Yang discusses gun reform in response to El Paso, Dayton shootings |publisher=[[MSNBC]] |access-date=August 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nTrump visited El Paso and Dayton on August 7. In Dayton, he spoke to hospitalized victims, medical staff, and first responders. The White House published photos and videos of his trip, some of which showed him posing, smiling, and giving [[thumbs up]] gestures with his hosts.<ref>\n*{{cite news |last1=Parker |first1=Ashley |last2=Rucker |first2=Philip |last3=Johnson |first3=Jenna |last4=Sonmez |first4=Felicia |title=Trump attacks local leaders as he visits two cities grieving from mass shootings |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/trump-lashes-out-at-beto-orourke-and-the-media-ahead-of-visits-to-el-paso-and-dayton/2019/08/07/b0aa8afc-b8fb-11e9-b3b4-2bb69e8c4e39_story.html |website=[[The Washington Post]] |accessdate=August 9, 2019 |date=August 8, 2019}}\n*{{cite news |title=Self-promotion: Trump boasts of rally crowd size during hospital visit to console Texas massacre survivors |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2019/08/09/world/politics-diplomacy-world/self-promotion-trump-boasts-rally-crowd-size-hospital-visit-console-texas-massacre-survivors/ |website=[[Agence France Presse]] and [[Jiji Press]] |accessdate=August 9, 2019 |date=August 9, 2019}}</ref> He told reporters, \"We had an amazing day. The love, the respect for the office of the presidency {{ndash}} I wish you could have been in there to see it.\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Crowley |first1=Michael |last2=Haberman |first2=Maggie |last3=Smith |first3=Mitch |last4=Shear |first4=Michael |title=Trump Uses a Day of Healing to Deepen the Nation's Divisions |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/07/us/politics/trump-el-paso-dayton-shootings.html |website=[[The New York Times]] |accessdate=August 9, 2019 |date=August 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== International ===\nThe incident was mentioned by [[Pope Francis]] during a speech in [[St. Peter's Square]] on August 4, in which he condemned attacks on defenseless people and said he was spiritually close to the victims, the wounded and the families affected by the attacks that had \"bloodied [[2019 El Paso shooting|Texas]], [[Gilroy Garlic Festival shooting|California]], and Ohio\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-texas-shooting-pope-idUSKCN1UU0BC|title=Pope condemns spate of U.S. gun violence, prays for victims|date=2019-08-04|agency=Reuters|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref>\n\nIn response to the shooting, the [[Consulate General of Japan in Detroit]] issued a notice stating that no Asians had been injured and that \"Japanese residents should be aware of the potential for gunfire incidents everywhere in the United States, a [[gun culture in the United States|gun society]], and continue to pay close attention to safety measures.\"<ref name=\"nations\">{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2019/08/07/748971210/after-mass-shootings-other-nations-issue-caution-about-gun-society-in-u-s|first1=Scott|last1=Neuman|title=After Mass Shootings, Other Nations Issue Caution about 'Gun Society' in US|publisher=NPR|date=August 7, 2019|accessdate=August 7, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.anzen.mofa.go.jp/od/ryojiMailDetail.html?keyCd=74322|title=About Shooting Incidents in Dayton, Ohio|publisher=Consulate General of Japan in Detroit|date=August 4, 2019}}</ref> At least two other nations \u2013 [[Uruguay]] and [[Venezuela]] \u2014 issued similar travel warnings, with Uruguay's foreign ministry issuing a statement warning its citizens traveling in the U.S. \"to take precautions against growing indiscriminate violence, mostly for [[hate crime]]s, including [[racism]] and [[discrimination]],\" and Venezuela cautioning its citizens to postpone travel to the U.S. or to take precautions \"given the proliferation of acts of violence and crimes of indiscriminate hatred.\"<ref name=\"nations\"/>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Law|United States}}\n*[[List of mass shootings in the United States]]\n*[[Mass shootings in the United States]]\n*[[Gun violence in the United States]]\n\n{{-}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/05/us/dayton-shooting-victims.html ''The New York Times'' list of victims fatally shot]\n* {{Commons-inline}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dayton shooting, 2019}}\n[[Category:2019 in Ohio]]\n[[Category:2019 mass shootings in the United States]]\n[[Category:2010s crimes in Ohio]]\n[[Category:Attacks on bars]]\n[[Category:August 2019 crimes in the United States]]\n[[Category:Deaths by firearm in Ohio]]\n[[Category:History of Dayton, Ohio|2019 shooting]]\n[[Category:Mass murder in 2019]]\n[[Category:Mass murder in the United States]]\n[[Category:Mass shootings in Ohio]]\n[[Category:Mass shootings in the United States]]\n[[Category:Murder in Ohio]]\n", "name_user": "Nice4What", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Dayton_shooting"}
